00:01:06,475 --> 00:01:07,600
Let me go!

3
00:01:07,725 --> 00:01:10,017
Let me go!

4
00:01:10,308 --> 00:01:12,142
Leave me--

5
00:01:12,392 --> 00:01:13,392
Release me!

6
00:01:13,517 --> 00:01:15,225
Let go of me!

7
00:01:27,683 --> 00:01:29,975
It's confirmed, boss.
He's our target.

8
00:02:03,350 --> 00:02:05,808
No--

9
00:02:09,642 --> 00:02:11,433
Don't kill me.

10
00:02:29,017 --> 00:02:31,933
Hey! Ask him to text me
after transferring the money.

11
00:02:32,017 --> 00:02:33,017
Okay.

12
00:02:53,767 --> 00:02:56,267
Where is that guy?
What's he doing inside?

13
00:02:57,392 --> 00:02:58,975
He may land us in trouble.

14
00:02:59,058 --> 00:03:00,058
What, boss?

15
00:03:02,933 --> 00:03:05,017
- Boss, my foot!
- Okay, boss.

16
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:36,933
<i>Breaking news for our viewers!</i>

17
00:03:37,475 --> 00:03:41,142
<i>The news I'm about to share
has never happened earlier in this area.</i>

18
00:03:41,225 --> 00:03:43,225
<i>It's a rampage all around.</i>

19
00:03:43,308 --> 00:03:47,225
A hyena has been spotted here.

20
00:03:55,267 --> 00:03:59,767
Saffron TV will give you
live updates by the minute.

21
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,475
People from nearby villages
have gathered here.

22
00:04:02,558 --> 00:04:05,517
We have no idea
what the hyena is going to do.

23
00:04:14,475 --> 00:04:15,517
Tell me, Joshy.

24
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,120
Sathya, I'm trying to reach Parthiban.

25
00:04:17,183 --> 00:04:18,808
His phone is not reachable.
Where is he?

26
00:04:18,892 --> 00:04:21,100
He must have gone
to drop Siddhu at school.

27
00:04:21,392 --> 00:04:24,183
Try calling Siddhu.
His phone will be in the car.

28
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:26,850
If he gets in touch,
please ask him to call me.

29
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,267
Handle this properly!

30
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:30,225
Place a barricade there.
Hurry up!

31
00:04:30,308 --> 00:04:31,350
- Kumar.
- Sir?

32
00:04:31,433 --> 00:04:34,725
- What's happening?
- Sir, nothing's right here. Everything--

33
00:04:34,808 --> 00:04:36,642
Sir, nothing is right here.

34
00:04:36,725 --> 00:04:39,159
- If it continues, many will be injured.
- Whom have they sent?

35
00:04:39,183 --> 00:04:41,475
Two experts have come
from Wild Life SOS team.

36
00:04:41,558 --> 00:04:44,350
They've handled only cheetahs,
but this is a hyena.

37
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:46,600
Nobody knows how to handle this, sir.

38
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,100
Parthiban, we have a situation.
It's an emergency.

39
00:04:53,183 --> 00:04:54,683
Can you come here?

40
00:04:54,767 --> 00:04:57,767
All right, first, see the photo
that I've sent you.

41
00:05:03,350 --> 00:05:04,600
Footprints are large.

42
00:05:04,683 --> 00:05:08,183
Maybe it's a spotted hyena.
If so, it will be extremely ferocious.

43
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,475
Okay.
How soon can you get here?

44
00:05:26,183 --> 00:05:30,350
Promise me, you won't tell your mom
that you were late for school today.

45
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:35,142
You promise me that you won't tell mom

46
00:05:35,225 --> 00:05:37,892
that I took my phone to school
just for today.

47
00:05:40,058 --> 00:05:41,517
Please, Dad!

48
00:05:53,725 --> 00:05:55,767
The situation
is not under control, Parthiban.

49
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:57,767
Hyenas are social animals, Joshy.

50
00:05:58,308 --> 00:05:59,475
They live in packs.

51
00:05:59,892 --> 00:06:03,058
If a hyena is alone here,
either it has lost its way

52
00:06:03,142 --> 00:06:06,392
or the rest of its clan is dead.
People will fear it and try to kill it.

53
00:06:06,475 --> 00:06:07,909
But we have to think
how we can capture it alive.

54
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:10,850
If you think like your men,
it will feast on us happily.

55
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:13,308
What to do now?
What are you suggesting?

56
00:06:14,183 --> 00:06:15,183
Walkie-Talkie.

57
00:06:16,808 --> 00:06:19,475
- Hey, Channel 3. We are on Channel 3.
- Got it.

58
00:06:21,017 --> 00:06:23,392
Dad, I'll come along.
I'll be helpful.

59
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,767
Stay in the car, my dear son.

60
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:27,933
That will be the biggest help.

61
00:06:28,017 --> 00:06:30,308
I don't want to get chided by your mom.

62
00:06:30,392 --> 00:06:31,433
Okay?

63
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,767
Put it!
Put up the barricades.

64
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:37,183
Push it here, quickly.
Hurry up. Come on.

65
00:06:37,267 --> 00:06:39,243
- Why did you place the barricades?
- DFO's orders, sir.

66
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:40,475
Watch out.

67
00:06:40,558 --> 00:06:42,642
What are you looking at?
Do it now.

68
00:06:44,767 --> 00:06:47,058
Sir, why did you place
the barricades here?

69
00:06:47,142 --> 00:06:50,183
The animal will barge into the school.
It's very risky. Please remove it.

70
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:52,017
Ranger, listen to me.

71
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:55,642
I'll give you my uniform.
Do my job as well.

72
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:58,017
Hey! What are you all looking at?

73
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,868
- Place the barricade properly.
- Come in, Parthiban.

74
00:06:59,892 --> 00:07:02,558
- Yeah, Joshy.
- They think it's a joke. Such a mess!

75
00:07:02,642 --> 00:07:04,451
I don't know what to do.
The situation is out of control.

76
00:07:04,475 --> 00:07:06,725
Get a tranquilizer from the sanctuary.

77
00:07:06,808 --> 00:07:08,201
I'll tell you when to fire
and from where.

78
00:07:08,225 --> 00:07:09,350
Yes, okay.

79
00:07:11,725 --> 00:07:13,975
Catch it--

80
00:07:16,558 --> 00:07:19,392
It's scared and is looking
for a place to hide.

81
00:07:19,475 --> 00:07:21,409
They are trying to kill it
without understanding that.

82
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:23,284
If this continues,
the hyena will enter the school.

83
00:07:23,308 --> 00:07:25,892
Bring the tranquilizer
to the west end of the school.

84
00:07:25,975 --> 00:07:28,017
Help!

85
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:31,517
Help--

86
00:07:31,808 --> 00:07:33,475
All the kids should go in!

87
00:07:33,558 --> 00:07:35,475
All the kids should go in!

88
00:07:35,558 --> 00:07:37,683
Kids, get inside!

89
00:07:45,850 --> 00:07:48,683
Students,
go to your classrooms immediately.

90
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:51,392
It's an emergency!
Teachers and staff!

91
00:07:51,475 --> 00:07:54,267
Please take all the children
safely into the classroom.

92
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:56,058
There is no time.
Hurry up!

93
00:08:00,058 --> 00:08:01,808
Get in--

94
00:08:03,183 --> 00:08:04,975
Go. Get in!

95
00:08:06,558 --> 00:08:08,975
I got permission for a tranquilizer gun.
I'm taking it, okay?

96
00:08:09,058 --> 00:08:10,225
Okay, sir.

97
00:09:02,183 --> 00:09:03,558
<i>Parthiban.</i>

98
00:09:03,975 --> 00:09:05,392
<i>I'm in position.</i>

99
00:09:06,683 --> 00:09:07,892
Joshy, wait!

100
00:09:07,975 --> 00:09:10,600
Don't aim at its neck
like our usual procedure.

101
00:09:10,683 --> 00:09:14,600
Its striking force will be as heavy
as its pitch of laughter.

102
00:09:14,683 --> 00:09:16,058
Aim for the lungs!

103
00:09:21,892 --> 00:09:23,308
Shoot.

104
00:09:28,225 --> 00:09:29,267
Darn.

105
00:09:29,558 --> 00:09:32,433
- Hang on.
- This is the perfect time. Shoot, Joshy.

106
00:09:33,850 --> 00:09:35,683
The gun is jammed, Parthiban.

107
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:39,558
A gun can't adapt
to the situation and operate.

108
00:09:39,642 --> 00:09:42,308
It's a machine.
You need to service it every month.

109
00:09:42,392 --> 00:09:43,267
- Siddhu?
- Dad.

110
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:44,475
Get your spear.

111
00:09:44,558 --> 00:09:47,267
- Give your shoe lace to Joshy.
- Okay, Dad.

112
00:09:52,475 --> 00:09:55,642
- Don't go--
- Run away.

113
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:23,975
You heard your dad, right?

114
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:26,433
Give me your shoe laces.

115
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:48,392
- Uncle, give the javelin to me.
- What?

116
00:11:02,683 --> 00:11:03,683
Get inside!

117
00:11:03,725 --> 00:11:05,183
Let's go!

118
00:11:17,933 --> 00:11:20,517
<i>Parthiban, the spear you asked for
is on its way.</i>

119
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:24,142
- Tell my dad that I'm throwing it.
- Parthiban, here it comes!

120
00:12:32,350 --> 00:12:34,392
Hey, come on, move.

121
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,725
Who is that man?

122
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:40,267
His name is Parthiban.

123
00:12:40,475 --> 00:12:42,058
He's from Tamil Nadu.

124
00:12:42,558 --> 00:12:43,767
Animal rescuer.

125
00:12:44,350 --> 00:12:46,100
He runs a coffee shop nearby.

126
00:12:47,142 --> 00:12:48,142
Hey!

127
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:50,017
- Get inside.
- Please, sir.

128
00:12:51,642 --> 00:12:53,392
Come on, start.

129
00:12:54,308 --> 00:12:56,850
Wait a minute.

130
00:12:56,975 --> 00:12:59,892
Ask the questions in an order.
The DFO will answer you.

131
00:12:59,975 --> 00:13:03,767
Look. This issue is not something
out of the ordinary.

132
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,392
It is our daily job.

133
00:13:05,475 --> 00:13:07,159
Animals migrate
in search of food and water--

134
00:13:07,183 --> 00:13:09,743
We've got exclusive news.
Why are you here instead of covering it?

135
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:13,433
There's nothing to cover here.
These forest officers didn't do anything.

136
00:13:13,517 --> 00:13:15,975
A middle-aged man in a white shirt
that was tucked in.

137
00:13:16,058 --> 00:13:19,017
Find him and get
the real information from him.

138
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:20,475
That is exclusive.

139
00:13:20,558 --> 00:13:22,100
- White shirt. Middle-aged man?
- Yes.

140
00:13:22,183 --> 00:13:24,183
Where do I find him in this crowd?

141
00:13:36,683 --> 00:13:38,392
<i>♪ Thalapathy ♪</i>

142
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:45,683
<i>♪ His entry spells power ♪</i>

143
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:47,642
<i>♪ Who is our brother?
Thalapathy! ♪</i>

144
00:14:02,892 --> 00:14:04,308
You wanted a shirt urgently.

145
00:14:04,392 --> 00:14:05,618
- What happened, sir?
- Stitch it and bring it.

146
00:14:05,642 --> 00:14:08,225
- What's this? It's blood-stained.
- Stitch it.

