177
00:15:39,225 --> 00:15:40,725
<i>♪ Yeah, I'm just a-- ♪</i>

178
00:15:40,808 --> 00:15:43,892
Sir, this shirt is ripped badly.
It can't be stitched.

179
00:15:43,975 --> 00:15:46,350
Do you know which shop
my wife bought this from?

180
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,850
- I don't know.
- I'm in trouble.

181
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:55,517
Hey, what's going on?
How did the police get our photos?

182
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,683
They are checking
at the borders and checkpoints.

183
00:15:57,767 --> 00:16:01,058
<i>The men who told us to kill the collector
betrayed us and double-crossed us.</i>

184
00:16:01,142 --> 00:16:02,933
<i>Not only that, they leaked our photos.</i>

185
00:16:03,017 --> 00:16:06,267
<i>Don't go out for a week.
Hide yourself.</i>

186
00:16:06,350 --> 00:16:07,767
<i>Please don't get caught.</i>

187
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:09,558
<i>Meanwhile, I'll do something.
Stay hidden.</i>

188
00:16:09,642 --> 00:16:12,308
What do you mean?
Where can we go right away?

189
00:16:12,392 --> 00:16:14,784
The four of us have no clue where we are
and what is happening.

190
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:16,975
We trusted you and came here,
you got us into trouble.

191
00:16:17,058 --> 00:16:18,100
Do you think I'm mad?

192
00:16:18,183 --> 00:16:20,017
We can't go anywhere
with our pockets empty.

193
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:22,350
We can't hide anywhere.
Arrange for us to come there.

194
00:16:22,433 --> 00:16:23,850
<i>Please understand the situation.</i>

195
00:16:23,933 --> 00:16:26,058
<i>All those against the collector
are being targeted.</i>

196
00:16:26,142 --> 00:16:28,534
<i>It will take more than a week
to get support from the center.</i>

197
00:16:28,558 --> 00:16:29,850
<i>Don't call up till I call you.</i>

198
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:31,558
- <i>Bye!</i>
- Hey--

199
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,725
Hey! Why are you looking at me?
Eyes on the road!

200
00:16:37,808 --> 00:16:38,892
What, boss?

201
00:16:49,850 --> 00:16:51,975
<i>In the early hours of yesterday morning,</i>

202
00:16:52,058 --> 00:16:55,183
<i>some unknown men broke
into the collector's guesthouse</i>

203
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:56,867
<i>have throat-slit and brutally murdered--</i>

204
00:16:56,892 --> 00:16:58,183
You didn't get ready yet?

205
00:16:59,142 --> 00:17:00,392
Oh, my shirt?

206
00:17:00,475 --> 00:17:06,642
I spilt chocolate on it,
so I put it to wash and changed--

207
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:16,683
I bought you that shirt
for our anniversary with so much love.

208
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:19,308
You've ruined it in every way possible.

209
00:17:19,392 --> 00:17:21,558
I have nothing to say now, let it be.

210
00:17:21,975 --> 00:17:25,100
My mood won't change today
no matter what excuse you give.

211
00:17:25,183 --> 00:17:26,475
Do whatever you want.

212
00:17:26,767 --> 00:17:28,475
There's no change in my plan.

213
00:17:50,683 --> 00:17:52,350
I'm leaving in an angry mood.

214
00:17:54,392 --> 00:17:58,683
<i>♪ Half of my soul is yours for infinity ♪</i>

215
00:18:00,142 --> 00:18:04,433
<i>♪ Half of yours is mine for eternity ♪</i>

216
00:18:05,808 --> 00:18:10,017
<i>♪ Only love as weapon is the counterpart ♪</i>

217
00:18:10,725 --> 00:18:13,475
<i>♪ In a brave warrior's heart ♪</i>

218
00:18:17,225 --> 00:18:19,850
<i>♪ Though my hair has streaks of gray-- ♪</i>

219
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,183
Shall we pick up the kids from school?

220
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:24,600
<i>♪ You are the love of my life-- ♪</i>

221
00:18:24,683 --> 00:18:25,850
- Excuse me.
- Excuse me.

222
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:26,975
- Yes.
- Hi.

223
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,142
Yes, tell me.

224
00:18:28,767 --> 00:18:29,933
Chintu--

225
00:18:30,142 --> 00:18:33,017
M-Mathi's mother is unwell.

226
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:35,058
Siddharth's father isn't well.

227
00:18:35,142 --> 00:18:36,725
I want to take her home.

228
00:18:36,808 --> 00:18:38,808
- Who are you?
- His mom.

229
00:18:39,058 --> 00:18:40,058
Her dad.

230
00:18:40,142 --> 00:18:44,017
<i>♪ If pure dew unites with a storm volatile ♪</i>

231
00:18:45,808 --> 00:18:49,683
<i>♪ Love's warmth will protect all the while ♪</i>

232
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:52,475
<i>♪ Only love-- ♪</i>

233
00:18:52,558 --> 00:18:55,058
- A small peg?
- No, I don't drink.

234
00:18:55,142 --> 00:18:57,933
- It's healthy and good for the weather.
- Really?

235
00:19:03,975 --> 00:19:06,433
- How do you drink this, sir?
- True that!

236
00:19:16,142 --> 00:19:17,558
Dad.

237
00:19:18,225 --> 00:19:20,517
We will be adopting this hyena.

238
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:24,100
What name would you suggest for it?

239
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:25,808
Elsa.

240
00:19:26,808 --> 00:19:27,808
Ghost.

241
00:19:28,642 --> 00:19:29,475
Hachiku.

242
00:19:29,558 --> 00:19:32,558
I'll suggest a name,
but you guys shouldn't laugh.

243
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:36,017
Actually, Subramani sounds good, right?

244
