01:47:44,850 --> 01:47:47,767
I'm not sure
if we can find a similar horoscope

1424
01:47:47,933 --> 01:47:50,433
with the same star and date of birth, Das.

1425
01:48:02,142 --> 01:48:05,308
Hey! Is there no other way?

1426
01:48:05,642 --> 01:48:07,975
Can't you come up with any other option?

1427
01:48:23,142 --> 01:48:24,933
I feel really sad to say this.

1428
01:48:26,433 --> 01:48:27,975
If you ask for my opinion,

1429
01:48:29,642 --> 01:48:31,058
I'll choose Leo.

1430
01:48:33,517 --> 01:48:34,517
No.

1431
01:48:35,808 --> 01:48:38,142
The decision-- the decision is all yours.

1432
01:48:38,225 --> 01:48:41,933
<i>♪ Garnished with spice and pepper
Oh, look! It boils with a special flavor ♪</i>

1433
01:48:42,017 --> 01:48:43,933
<i>♪ Those limbs so amazing and super ♪</i>

1434
01:48:44,058 --> 01:48:47,433
<i>♪ Fist fight that strikes like lightning
Flashes into our kitchen and dining ♪</i>

1435
01:48:47,517 --> 01:48:49,183
<i>♪ Inviting and awakening ♪</i>

1436
01:48:49,267 --> 01:48:52,808
<i>♪ Many a knife waiting to stab me ♪</i>

1437
01:48:52,892 --> 01:48:54,767
<i>♪ That's their account to tally ♪</i>

1438
01:48:54,850 --> 01:48:58,100
<i>♪ This knife is different altogether
Don't you dare plan to close my chapter ♪</i>

1439
01:48:58,183 --> 01:49:00,558
- <i>♪ Do you get it, mister? ♪
- ♪ Oh! Yes, master. ♪</i>

1440
01:49:10,892 --> 01:49:13,517
<i>♪ I'm known by another name too ♪</i>

1441
01:49:13,600 --> 01:49:16,350
<i>♪ You'll tremble in fear
Upon hearing it, dude ♪</i>

1442
01:49:16,433 --> 01:49:19,100
<i>♪ Print out the poster
All-ready is your brother ♪</i>

1443
01:49:19,225 --> 01:49:21,433
<i>♪ Celebrate and how!
Set it ablaze now ♪</i>

1444
01:49:21,892 --> 01:49:23,225
<i>♪ Here I am-- ♪</i>

1445
01:49:23,308 --> 01:49:24,808
<i>♪ Hey! Make way for our bro! ♪</i>

1446
01:49:31,183 --> 01:49:33,933
<i>♪ Here I am, your dear bro.
Shall I come now? ♪</i>

1447
01:49:34,308 --> 01:49:36,767
<i>♪ Don't taunt this lion
With the sting of a scorpion ♪</i>

1448
01:49:36,850 --> 01:49:39,618
<i>♪ No matter who tries to obstruct my route
It will be the same forever ♪</i>

1449
01:49:39,642 --> 01:49:42,058
<i>♪ I'm ready.
Shall I make an entry? ♪</i>

1450
01:49:42,142 --> 01:49:44,642
<i>♪ Your favorite bro, shall I come solo? ♪</i>

1451
01:49:44,725 --> 01:49:47,701
<i>♪ Till the Earth quakes, beat the drum
I will dance in tune to your rhythm ♪</i>

1452
01:49:47,725 --> 01:49:50,850
<i>♪ I'll light the torch in a flick
Between my fingers double quick ♪</i>

1453
01:49:55,808 --> 01:50:00,558
<i>♪ Pick the best goat and slaughter
So I can appease my hunger ♪</i>

1454
01:50:53,267 --> 01:50:55,308
I had to do this, Leo.

1455
01:50:56,558 --> 01:50:58,767
Even now, between you and your sister

1456
01:50:59,183 --> 01:51:02,767
many chose you,
they opted to sacrifice you.

1457
01:51:02,850 --> 01:51:04,725
My brother also chose you.

1458
01:51:05,808 --> 01:51:08,850
I was the one who saved you!

1459
01:51:10,267 --> 01:51:12,225
You need not thank me for that.

1460
01:51:14,558 --> 01:51:16,017
Just pardon me.

1461
01:51:17,600 --> 01:51:19,767
From my childhood till date,

1462
01:51:19,850 --> 01:51:22,933
I've killed countless people
for your sake.

1463
01:51:24,017 --> 01:51:27,433
I took your word as gospel
and killed my friend too.

1464
01:51:29,058 --> 01:51:31,142
That was for our business.

1465
01:51:32,600 --> 01:51:35,975
But this is mere superstition!

1466
01:51:36,100 --> 01:51:38,183
Let go of Elisa!

1467
01:51:38,392 --> 01:51:40,142
Leo!

1468
01:51:40,308 --> 01:51:42,600
This is also for our business.

1469
01:51:43,892 --> 01:51:46,517
- Understand that!
- Hey!

1470
01:51:49,725 --> 01:51:51,767
She isn't just my sister.

1471
01:51:53,267 --> 01:51:56,808
She is my twin.
A part of me, my other half!

1472
01:51:57,308 --> 01:51:59,642
If anything untoward happens to her,

1473
01:51:59,808 --> 01:52:01,975
no matter how many births you take

1474
01:52:02,683 --> 01:52:07,017
the day I see you will be your last day!

1475
01:52:07,475 --> 01:52:09,308
The day I meet you

1476
01:52:09,392 --> 01:52:12,683
will be your last day on Earth!

1477
01:52:13,600 --> 01:52:15,100
Are you begging him?

1478
01:52:17,600 --> 01:52:19,725
Didn't I tell you the day
our mother passed away?

1479
01:52:19,808 --> 01:52:22,683
That he has something
to do with her death.

1480
01:52:22,767 --> 01:52:25,683
If he has decided
to sacrifice his children,

1481
01:52:26,308 --> 01:52:27,767
I don't consider him my dad anymore,

1482
01:52:27,850 --> 01:52:30,100
none of them here are my kith and kin!

1483
01:52:31,183 --> 01:52:32,892
Will you do me a favor, Leo?

1484
01:52:34,558 --> 01:52:37,558
Don't spare any of them alive.

1485
01:52:52,392 --> 01:52:53,642
Hey!

1486
01:52:54,558 --> 01:52:56,183
Don't even think about it.

1487
01:52:59,350 --> 01:53:00,725
Hey!

1488
01:53:01,892 --> 01:53:03,142
Hey!

1489
01:53:03,267 --> 01:53:04,933
Don't you dare!

1490
01:53:05,183 --> 01:53:06,642
Let her go!

1491
01:53:06,725 --> 01:53:08,350
Dad!

1492
01:53:08,600 --> 01:53:10,350
Dad!

1493
01:53:11,517 --> 01:53:12,850
Hey!

1494
01:53:12,933 --> 01:53:15,475
Release her!
Let her go!

1495
01:53:33,725 --> 01:53:35,892
Elisa, try to understand!

1496
01:53:36,642 --> 01:53:37,892
Understand my plight!

1497
01:53:41,767 --> 01:53:43,767
Leo!

1498
01:53:47,892 --> 01:53:49,392
Hey!

1499
01:53:52,308 --> 01:53:54,308
Leo, burn down the entire factory.

1500
01:53:54,392 --> 01:53:56,142
Harold, don't let them escape.

1501
01:53:57,892 --> 01:54:01,725
Harold!
Don't let them escape!

1502
01:54:11,642 --> 01:54:12,725
Leo!

1503
01:54:22,100 --> 01:54:25,142
- Come on.
- Come!

1504
01:54:31,017 --> 01:54:33,308
- Come on.
- Catch--

1505
01:54:37,683 --> 01:54:39,808
Hey! Don't spare anyone.

1506
01:55:03,642 --> 01:55:06,558
Don't leave anything out!
Burn everything down!

1507
01:55:06,642 --> 01:55:07,808
Everything!

1508
01:55:45,017 --> 01:55:46,433
Hey!

1509
01:55:46,683 --> 01:55:47,725
Hey!

1510
01:55:48,767 --> 01:55:52,058
You wanted to sacrifice
your children for this, right?

1511
01:55:53,433 --> 01:55:54,475
Hey, Leo!

1512
01:55:54,558 --> 01:55:56,058
This shouldn't exist anymore!

1513
01:55:56,142 --> 01:55:57,558
Hereafter this--

1514
01:55:58,017 --> 01:55:59,225
Hey!

1515
01:55:59,350 --> 01:56:00,808
--shouldn't exist!

1516
01:56:00,892 --> 01:56:02,600
Leo, stop it!

1517
01:56:05,975 --> 01:56:07,892
Hey! Throw me a knife.

1518
01:56:13,558 --> 01:56:17,017
Elisa!

1519
01:56:25,933 --> 01:56:28,892
Elisa--

1520
01:56:30,017 --> 01:56:32,558
- Elisa--
- Leo.

1521
01:56:34,475 --> 01:56:36,433
Don't be with them, Leo.

1522
01:56:36,517 --> 01:56:37,600
Elisa!

1523
01:56:37,850 --> 01:56:39,767
Go somewhere far away.

1524
01:57:38,100 --> 01:57:39,392
My dearest Elisa!

1525
01:57:40,017 --> 01:57:42,350
Elisa!

1526
01:57:45,183 --> 01:57:47,058
Elisa!

1527
01:58:13,267 --> 01:58:14,767
I raised him.

1528
01:58:14,850 --> 01:58:18,517
The day he collapsed and burned
to his death in front of my eyes

1529
01:58:18,600 --> 01:58:21,017
is embedded in my heart.

1530
01:58:25,767 --> 01:58:28,517
Tell me if it's Leo in this photo.

1531
01:58:30,183 --> 01:58:31,058
No need.

1532
01:58:31,142 --> 01:58:34,475
If you just identify him,
all the problems will be solved.

1533
01:58:38,683 --> 01:58:40,975
Even if he stands amidst 1,000 people,

1534
01:58:41,058 --> 01:58:43,517
I can identify Leo from his eyes.

1535
01:58:43,933 --> 01:58:45,100
This isn't him.

1536
01:58:45,308 --> 01:58:48,142
Don't play unnecessarily
with an innocent man's life.

1537
01:58:48,225 --> 01:58:50,808
Warden!
Take me away.

1538
01:58:50,933 --> 01:58:53,433
He is shell-shocked
upon hearing one day's happenings.

1539
01:58:53,517 --> 01:58:56,933
If he hears the entire story,
he's likely to lose his life!

1540
01:59:02,225 --> 01:59:03,225
Give it.

1541
01:59:04,767 --> 01:59:09,017
We clicked this during third grade.
This is in fourth grade.

1542
01:59:09,392 --> 01:59:10,975
And this is in fifth grade.

1543
01:59:11,642 --> 01:59:14,267
This is the letter he wrote to me
during his college days.

1544
01:59:20,683 --> 01:59:22,267
May I ask you something?

1545
01:59:22,350 --> 01:59:24,683
I consider you my brother
and I'm asking you this.

1546
01:59:24,767 --> 01:59:28,975
I know what's on your mind.
I won't tell him about your visit.

1547
01:59:29,058 --> 01:59:30,808
Make sure that he doesn't find out.

1548
01:59:30,892 --> 01:59:33,058
If he finds out, he'll be devastated.

1549
01:59:37,600 --> 01:59:39,808
- Hello?
- <i>Sir, is this Parthiban?</i>

1550
01:59:39,975 --> 01:59:42,267
- Yes.
- <i>Sir, come to the coffee shop at once.</i>

1551
01:59:42,350 --> 01:59:43,392
<i>It's an emergency.</i>

1552
01:59:45,517 --> 01:59:48,517
He was drinking with us, sir.

1553
01:59:48,725 --> 01:59:51,433
I don't know why he kept saying
that he saw his friend.

1554
01:59:51,517 --> 01:59:53,183
He was happily drinking.

1555
01:59:53,267 --> 01:59:55,225
He even bought booze
for all the passers-by, sir.

1556
01:59:55,308 --> 01:59:57,767
Then he left in an inebriated state.

1557
01:59:57,850 --> 02:00:00,118
He stood on the road and spoke to someone
over the phone for a long time.

1558
02:00:00,142 --> 02:00:02,350
Then some people arrived in a car
and took him away.

1559
02:00:02,517 --> 02:00:04,350
- Was it a black car?
- Yes, sir.

1560
02:00:11,808 --> 02:00:12,850
Hey!

1561
02:00:16,100 --> 02:00:18,267
He claimed to be your friend
and came to your cafe.

1562
02:00:18,350 --> 02:00:21,475
He sat there and chatted with you.
He has even taken your photo.

1563
02:00:21,558 --> 02:00:24,558
How do you know him?
Can't you hear me?

1564
02:00:27,433 --> 02:00:31,558
Sir! If he was a regular customer at my cafe,

1565
02:00:31,642 --> 02:00:34,392
I should've at least been
slightly upset, right?

1566
02:00:35,642 --> 02:00:37,767
Look into my eyes.
Are there tears?

1567
02:00:39,100 --> 02:00:40,892
I don't know him, sir.

1568
02:00:41,267 --> 02:00:44,683
How can I be responsible
for him dying in front of my cafe?

1569
02:00:44,767 --> 02:00:48,767
I'll come to the station when you call me.
You can interrogate me there.

1570
02:00:48,850 --> 02:00:52,183
I've left my little girl alone at home.
I'm scared for her. I need to go.

1571
02:00:52,267 --> 02:00:54,517
- Okay, go.
- Thank you, sir.

1572
02:01:23,683 --> 02:01:27,350
I don't know whether to feel sorry
or be suspicious of Parthiban.

1573
02:01:27,433 --> 02:01:28,600
Listen.

1574
02:01:28,725 --> 02:01:33,100
Every human being
has a limit to lie and pretend.

1575
02:01:33,392 --> 02:01:35,142
He can do it only up to a breaking point.

1576
02:01:35,225 --> 02:01:39,433
He can't continue to put on an act
beyond that point.

1577
02:01:40,100 --> 02:01:42,642
Because no one is mentally strong
to that extent.

1578
02:01:42,725 --> 02:01:45,892
I feel Parthiban isn't acting.

1579
02:01:45,975 --> 02:01:47,558
He is Parthiban indeed.

1580
02:01:48,392 --> 02:01:50,558
Beyond this, if truth has to be told,

1581
02:01:51,058 --> 02:01:54,517
Leo, who is allegedly dead
has to come in person and say it.

1582
02:01:55,975 --> 02:01:57,225
Parthi, are you back?

1583
02:01:57,308 --> 02:01:59,558
I heard you left in a hurry
because you got a call.

1584
02:01:59,642 --> 02:02:00,683
Where did you go?

1585
02:02:00,767 --> 02:02:02,868
Do you know how hectic the past two days
have been at work for me?

1586
02:02:02,892 --> 02:02:05,100
Why is your dinner untouched?

1587
02:02:05,392 --> 02:02:09,433
Parthi, what happened?
Why are you sitting here quietly?

1588
02:02:25,308 --> 02:02:29,350
Beyond this,
I have nothing left to lose, dear.

1589
02:02:30,683 --> 02:02:34,267
I'm a loser.

1590
02:02:37,517 --> 02:02:40,433
From my fingerprints
to the black pupils of my eyes,

1591
02:02:40,517 --> 02:02:42,225
you are suspecting every part of me.

1592
02:02:42,308 --> 02:02:44,350
- It's not like that, please--
- Don't touch me!

1593
02:02:44,433 --> 02:02:46,017
Don't touch me.

1594
02:02:49,475 --> 02:02:52,475
This whole world can suspect me.

1595
02:02:52,558 --> 02:02:56,725
But how could you doubt me?
How did you see me as a stranger?

1596
02:02:56,808 --> 02:02:57,933
Sathya?

1597
02:03:03,933 --> 02:03:07,850
Oh, no! No matter what
explanation you give to appease me,

1598
02:03:09,100 --> 02:03:12,100
the fact that you suspected me

1599
02:03:12,183 --> 02:03:14,725
will haunt me forever.

1600
02:03:15,225 --> 02:03:16,558
Is our bond so fragile?

1601
02:03:16,642 --> 02:03:19,808
The life that we led so far
has lost its meaning.

1602
02:03:19,892 --> 02:03:20,933
That's it, right?

1603
02:03:25,475 --> 02:03:27,600
I am not him!

1604
02:03:27,933 --> 02:03:30,267
Parthiban isn't that kind of a person.

1605
02:03:30,350 --> 02:03:33,142
Despite repeating myself
over and over again,

1606
02:03:33,517 --> 02:03:36,433
just because some
random chap resembles me--

1607
02:03:39,683 --> 02:03:41,159
- What happened, Dad?
- It's nothing, sweetie.

1608
02:03:41,183 --> 02:03:44,433
I wasn't feeling well.
Go to sleep.

1609
02:03:44,642 --> 02:03:47,600
<i>♪ Dance for me. Oh-- ♪</i>

1610
02:03:47,683 --> 02:03:51,308
<i>♪ I've never seen anybody do the things
you do before ♪</i>

1611
02:03:51,392 --> 02:03:54,475
<i>♪ They say, move for me ♪</i>

1612
02:03:54,600 --> 02:03:59,433
<i>♪ And when you're done,
I'll make you do it all again ♪</i>

1613
02:04:01,183 --> 02:04:03,350
Hey, you.

1614
02:04:04,558 --> 02:04:06,392
Some random fellow--

1615
02:04:07,600 --> 02:04:11,267
If they torture me claiming
I resemble some random riff-raff,

1616
02:04:11,350 --> 02:04:13,100
what can I do?

1617
02:04:13,433 --> 02:04:16,308
You've forsaken your trust in me.

1618
02:04:16,392 --> 02:04:18,558
My son asked me if I'm his dad.

1619
02:04:18,642 --> 02:04:22,142
You ask me if I'm your husband!
Who am I? Tell me.

1620
02:04:25,517 --> 02:04:26,683
That's correct.

1621
02:04:27,225 --> 02:04:30,767
I don't know who my parents are
or what my place of birth is.

1622
02:04:30,892 --> 02:04:32,308
I'm an orphan.

1623
02:04:32,850 --> 02:04:35,933
Maybe if they were alive,
they wouldn't have suspected me.

1624
02:04:36,017 --> 02:04:37,142
I'm an orphan, after all.

1625
02:04:37,225 --> 02:04:38,683
- Don't say that.
- Just an orphan.

1626
02:04:38,767 --> 02:04:42,017
Parthi, you're not an orphan.
Look at me.

1627
02:04:42,267 --> 02:04:44,433
I'm telling you to look into my eyes.

1628
02:04:44,850 --> 02:04:47,767
I didn't do this
due to lack of trust in you.

1629
02:04:47,850 --> 02:04:51,808
When other people ask me,
I need to tell them with certainty, right?

1630
02:04:52,225 --> 02:04:53,725
"He is not that man."

1631
02:04:53,850 --> 02:04:56,743
I should be able to confidently assert
this is my husband, Parthiban, right?

1632
02:04:56,767 --> 02:04:58,850
Why can't you understand?

1633
02:05:00,600 --> 02:05:01,725
My dear.

1634
02:05:02,558 --> 02:05:05,558
I need to ask just one question.

1635
02:05:06,308 --> 02:05:09,767
After you suspected
that I was someone else,

1636
02:05:10,475 --> 02:05:13,225
how could you touch me with familiarity?

1637
02:05:13,850 --> 02:05:15,350
Wouldn't you feel disgusted?

1638
02:05:15,433 --> 02:05:17,183
The way actress Revathi
says in <i>Mouna Ragam</i>,

1639
02:05:17,267 --> 02:05:20,183
"I feel a hairy caterpillar
is crawling all over--"

1640
02:05:27,308 --> 02:05:28,725
Trust me.

1641
02:05:30,558 --> 02:05:31,850
Sathya.

1642
02:05:35,100 --> 02:05:36,683
Please trust me.

1643
02:05:37,808 --> 02:05:40,808
I'm your Parthi, dear.

1644
02:05:53,558 --> 02:05:56,558
<i>Leo, the time I gave you is over.</i>

1645
02:05:56,725 --> 02:05:59,683
<i>You didn't come.
So I am here to see you.</i>

1646
02:05:59,767 --> 02:06:00,850
<i>Look outside.</i>

1647
02:06:05,308 --> 02:06:07,308
Hey! Who the hell are you all?

1648
02:06:07,683 --> 02:06:09,183
What are you doing here?

1649
02:06:09,392 --> 02:06:10,975
You better leave!

1650
02:06:11,058 --> 02:06:12,725
I'll shoot you all down!

1651
02:06:12,808 --> 02:06:14,808
You won't leave this place alive!

1652
02:06:18,100 --> 02:06:20,392
<i>This need not have gone so far.</i>

1653
02:06:20,517 --> 02:06:24,642
If you had come of your own accord
and admitted to me that you are Leo

1654
02:06:25,308 --> 02:06:27,892
I wouldn't have come here now.

1655
02:06:28,058 --> 02:06:30,392
Sir! Don't come downstairs
for any reason whatsoever.

1656
02:06:30,475 --> 02:06:31,767
I'll deal with them!

1657
02:06:32,183 --> 02:06:34,183
I came to meet you

1658
02:06:34,350 --> 02:06:37,433
but a mongrel is barking over here!

1659
02:06:39,475 --> 02:06:40,475
Okay.

1660
02:06:40,600 --> 02:06:44,350
Amidst all this, give some thought
to where your son is.

1661
02:06:45,683 --> 02:06:46,892
Sathya?

1662
02:06:46,975 --> 02:06:48,058
Where is Siddharth?

1663
02:06:48,142 --> 02:06:49,933
- What happened?
- Where is Siddhu?

1664
02:06:50,017 --> 02:06:51,951
- Check on Siddhu.
- <i>You won't be able to find him.</i>

1665
02:06:51,975 --> 02:06:54,767
- <i>He would've reached his destination.</i>
- He isn't here!

1666
02:06:54,850 --> 02:06:55,892
Siddharth!

1667
02:06:56,433 --> 02:06:58,558
Bring our daughter.

1668
02:06:58,850 --> 02:07:02,100
But your son is so damn cute.

1669
02:07:02,308 --> 02:07:05,642
<i>He came out to smoke, got trapped
and made it easy for us.</i>

1670
02:07:06,058 --> 02:07:07,558
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

1671
02:07:07,975 --> 02:07:10,850
Parthiban, what is happening here?
Where is Siddhu?

1672
02:07:11,850 --> 02:07:13,267
Whom are you talking to?

1673
02:07:13,350 --> 02:07:15,767
If anyone except me enters the house,
you must stab them.

1674
02:07:15,850 --> 02:07:16,767
Why?

1675
02:07:16,850 --> 02:07:19,183
You will do it.
Hold it! Come on!

1676
02:07:20,933 --> 02:07:22,725
Go in.

1677
02:07:22,808 --> 02:07:24,808
Lock the door from inside, Sathya.

1678
02:07:25,600 --> 02:07:27,308
<i>You don't have to be Leo.</i>

1679
02:07:27,392 --> 02:07:30,183
But think about it.

1680
02:07:30,267 --> 02:07:32,183
<i>Why should I kidnap your son?</i>

1681
02:07:32,725 --> 02:07:36,683
Twenty-two years ago, your sister died

1682
02:07:37,725 --> 02:07:39,475
on this very day.

1683
02:07:39,725 --> 02:07:42,350
<i>I'm taking your son today</i>

1684
02:07:42,808 --> 02:07:45,183
and you know the reason behind it.

1685
02:07:45,975 --> 02:07:49,850
Don't you understand?
I don't have a sister or any damn sibling.

1686
02:07:50,142 --> 02:07:52,183
Let go of my son, rascal!

1687
02:07:55,100 --> 02:07:58,392
- Sir?
- You'll come on your own, Leo!

1688
02:07:59,767 --> 02:08:02,558
- What is it?
- Sir, open the door!

1689
02:08:13,017 --> 02:08:16,642
- Sir, they have kidnapped Siddhu.
- I didn't know they took him.

1690
02:08:18,183 --> 02:08:19,642
Hey!

1691
02:08:40,267 --> 02:08:41,683
Load your gun, sir.

1692
02:09:18,058 --> 02:09:19,225
Sir, hold tight!

1693
02:09:21,558 --> 02:09:23,350
Watch out!

1694
02:11:01,767 --> 02:11:03,850
Where is my son!

1695
02:11:03,933 --> 02:11:06,142
Answer me!
Where is my son!

1696
02:11:23,225 --> 02:11:24,850
Hey!

1697
02:11:31,850 --> 02:11:32,850
Siddhu?

1698
02:11:33,142 --> 02:11:34,183
Siddhu?

1699
02:11:35,892 --> 02:11:37,058
Siddhu!

1700
02:12:14,517 --> 02:12:16,350
My son!

1701
02:12:26,642 --> 02:12:28,558
I failed to kill you, Leo.

1702
02:12:29,475 --> 02:12:32,142
But I won't fail to kill your son!

1703
02:12:45,058 --> 02:12:47,350
I'm not the man you're looking for!

1704
02:12:47,433 --> 02:12:50,392
You're presuming I'm your son
and ruining my life!

1705
02:12:53,392 --> 02:12:55,725
Where is my son?
Come on, tell me.

1706
02:12:55,892 --> 02:12:58,975
Speak up! Where is my son?
Tell me!

1707
02:13:00,850 --> 02:13:03,225
Accept that you're my son.

1708
02:13:05,392 --> 02:13:07,683
And I'll let your son go.

1709
02:13:07,767 --> 02:13:11,975
Oh, God!
I'm not your son! No.

1710
02:13:12,058 --> 02:13:13,642
I'm not your son!

1711
02:13:58,017 --> 02:13:59,225
Tell me.

1712
02:14:00,433 --> 02:14:01,975
You're my son, right?

1713
02:14:08,475 --> 02:14:12,850
Harold, Antony is no more.

1714
02:14:14,100 --> 02:14:15,975
I'm bringing the boy.

1715
02:14:18,058 --> 02:14:21,308
Napoleon needs bed-rest.
I'm there, I'll take care of him.

1716
02:14:21,392 --> 02:14:24,892
But they won't stop at this.
They will come looking for you.

1717
02:14:25,017 --> 02:14:26,808
Your son will be safe for now.

1718
02:14:27,100 --> 02:14:29,392
We will send a task force and find him.

1719
02:14:30,142 --> 02:14:32,183
But you shouldn't stay here.

1720
02:14:32,267 --> 02:14:34,892
If you stay here,
your life will be in grave danger.

1721
02:14:34,975 --> 02:14:36,267
Please listen to me.

1722
02:14:36,850 --> 02:14:39,850
I've arranged a car.
It's parked at your doorstep.

1723
02:14:39,933 --> 02:14:42,975
Collect your essentials and leave.
Now!

1724
02:14:47,433 --> 02:14:48,475
Who is this?

1725
02:14:55,225 --> 02:14:58,142
Leo, no matter where you go and hide

1726
02:14:58,350 --> 02:15:00,767
you know very well
that I'll come and get you.

1727
02:15:00,850 --> 02:15:02,350
<i>All I want is your life.</i>

1728
02:15:02,433 --> 02:15:04,683
Don't step on my ego and lose your family.

1729
02:15:04,767 --> 02:15:06,683
If you want your son back

1730
02:15:07,683 --> 02:15:09,683
hand over my elder brother to me.

1731
02:15:10,267 --> 02:15:13,392
Bring him here and take your son.

1732
02:15:24,600 --> 02:15:28,100
Parthiban, take it.
Go soon and bring back your son.

1733
02:15:50,683 --> 02:15:52,850
Das, I've sent boss' body.

1734
02:15:52,975 --> 02:15:56,517
We have boarded him on the train.
We will reach in an hour.

1735
02:16:54,225 --> 02:16:58,017
Sir, as per your request,
I've given your brother's body.

1736
02:16:58,475 --> 02:17:01,350
Please give my son back, I'll leave.

1737
02:17:03,975 --> 02:17:07,308
I know, you won't believe me
no matter what I say.

1738
02:17:07,725 --> 02:17:09,933
- That's why I--
- Hey!

1739
02:17:13,225 --> 02:17:16,100
Don't be scared.
This is just my son's school bag.

1740
02:17:16,433 --> 02:17:17,618
Sir, this is my birth certificate

1741
02:17:17,642 --> 02:17:19,159
and these are my 10th
and 12th mark sheets.

1742
02:17:19,183 --> 02:17:20,993
This is my ration card, Aadhar card
and wedding photos.

1743
02:17:21,017 --> 02:17:22,659
This was clicked during
my daughter's ear piercing ceremony.

1744
02:17:22,683 --> 02:17:24,493
This was clicked on my son's
first birthday, sir.

1745
02:17:24,517 --> 02:17:25,350
Look at this, sir.

1746
02:17:25,433 --> 02:17:27,618
When I was in 10th grade,
I took part in an oratorical contest

1747
02:17:27,642 --> 02:17:29,076
and bagged the first prize with my speech
on <i>Kappalottiya Thamizhan</i>.

1748
02:17:29,100 --> 02:17:30,517
This was taken there.

1749
02:17:30,600 --> 02:17:33,433
My name is in bold letters
in the certificate.

1750
02:17:40,892 --> 02:17:44,808
Look here. This is you and your sister
on your 10th birthday.

1751
02:17:44,892 --> 02:17:47,975
A Honey Badger
had entered our tobacco field.

1752
02:17:48,058 --> 02:17:49,933
This photo was taken after it was killed.

1753
02:17:50,017 --> 02:17:52,392
Look how smart you look
with that blood-stained face.

1754
02:17:52,475 --> 02:17:53,517
I understand, sir.

1755
02:17:54,683 --> 02:17:58,225
It's not wrong
that you mistook me for Leo, sir.

1756
02:17:58,308 --> 02:18:00,558
He bears a striking resemblance to me.

1757
02:18:03,350 --> 02:18:05,975
Hey! Do I look like a fool?

1758
02:18:07,642 --> 02:18:10,850
- Sir--
- Do I seem like an imbecile?

1759
02:18:12,725 --> 02:18:14,225
Leo.

1760
02:18:14,433 --> 02:18:17,767
You know what I did to your twin sister.

1761
02:18:17,933 --> 02:18:19,975
I think you haven't forgotten that.

1762
02:18:20,558 --> 02:18:23,017
You better accept that you are Leo.

1763
02:18:23,100 --> 02:18:25,808
Or your son will share
the same fate as your twin.

1764
02:18:25,892 --> 02:18:29,558
Sir, I don't have a sister.
How do I make you understand?

1765
02:18:29,642 --> 02:18:30,808
Siddhu?

1766
02:18:39,225 --> 02:18:40,558
Sir.

1767
02:18:43,308 --> 02:18:45,975
In all these years,
he is scrutinizing someone

1768
02:18:46,225 --> 02:18:48,058
for the first time.

1769
02:18:48,225 --> 02:18:52,100
Human beings can lie.
Certificates can be fake.

1770
02:18:52,725 --> 02:18:55,142
But birds and beasts never lie.

1771
02:18:55,225 --> 02:18:59,100
I've never seen an eagle
at such close quarters in my life, sir.

1772
02:18:59,517 --> 02:19:01,725
Ask it to step back.
I'm scared, sir.

1773
02:19:08,892 --> 02:19:09,767
Hey.

1774
02:19:09,850 --> 02:19:13,058
This performance
is just to protect your family, right?

1775
02:19:13,142 --> 02:19:15,308
You committed a blunder even there.

1776
02:19:15,725 --> 02:19:17,975
You came here to save your son

1777
02:19:18,058 --> 02:19:20,183
but left your wife and your daughter

1778
02:19:20,350 --> 02:19:22,600
all alone at home, my dear boy.

1779
02:19:23,350 --> 02:19:24,642
Shall I ask my men

1780
02:19:24,933 --> 02:19:29,558
to slit their throats?

1781
02:19:30,433 --> 02:19:31,433
Hey!

1782
02:19:32,475 --> 02:19:33,933
Okay, sir.

1783
02:19:43,808 --> 02:19:45,642
Sir, don't harm them.

1784
02:19:45,725 --> 02:19:47,183
Sir, please.

1785
02:19:58,767 --> 02:20:00,683
Hey!

1786
02:20:00,767 --> 02:20:04,142
Instruct your guys not to harm them, sir.
Poor souls, sir.

1787
02:20:12,475 --> 02:20:15,142
- Shut up!
- Hush!

1788
02:20:18,475 --> 02:20:20,183
Let's run for our lives!

1789
02:20:24,308 --> 02:20:26,725
What's this?
They have planted bombs here!

1790
02:20:27,767 --> 02:20:30,267
- What is it, Mom?
- Nothing, dear, go back to sleep.

1791
02:20:30,350 --> 02:20:33,017
Sir, tell them not to go in.

1792
02:20:33,100 --> 02:20:34,159
- Hey, what happened--
- Sir.

1793
02:20:34,183 --> 02:20:36,433
- Will you walk in the front?
- Shut up!

1794
02:20:39,267 --> 02:20:41,350
No, don't!

1795
02:20:42,683 --> 02:20:44,725
Hey! He's gone.

1796
02:20:48,142 --> 02:20:50,850
My eyes are burning!

1797
02:20:50,933 --> 02:20:52,767
It's burning!

1798
02:20:52,892 --> 02:20:53,975
Come with me.

1799
02:20:56,308 --> 02:20:58,100
Hey! You climb up.

1800
02:20:58,225 --> 02:21:00,392
What?
Can you open it or not?

1801
02:21:00,600 --> 02:21:01,683
Hey!

1802
02:21:01,892 --> 02:21:03,058
- Sir--
- Hey!

1803
02:21:03,142 --> 02:21:05,350
Sir, at least you tell him, please.

1804
02:21:05,433 --> 02:21:07,273
Tell them not to do anything, sir.
Please, sir.

1805
02:21:07,308 --> 02:21:10,142
Instruct them not to enter
my house, please, sir.

1806
02:21:18,767 --> 02:21:21,308
You're leaving me alone to face this!

1807
02:21:31,350 --> 02:21:33,683
- You climb up.
- Let's come back in the morning.

1808
02:21:33,767 --> 02:21:34,975
Hey! Just climb!

1809
02:21:46,225 --> 02:21:47,475
My side is all clear.

1810
02:21:47,558 --> 02:21:50,308
Check those who are entering
through the main door.

1811
02:21:50,392 --> 02:21:53,142
Watch it, there could be more booby traps.

1812
02:22:10,892 --> 02:22:13,142
Who is this?
Looks like Chhota Bheem.

1813
02:22:20,642 --> 02:22:22,767
Hey! Stupid guy, come!

1814
02:22:23,892 --> 02:22:24,975
Hey!

1815
02:23:07,183 --> 02:23:08,183
Sir.

1816
02:23:08,392 --> 02:23:11,933
I killed all those who barged in
except for one guy.

1817
02:23:12,017 --> 02:23:14,118
He climbed in from the side
and entered upstairs, sir.

1818
02:23:14,142 --> 02:23:15,725
<i>He will go to hell soon.</i>

1819
02:23:15,808 --> 02:23:17,058
<i>You be safe.</i>

1820
02:23:24,100 --> 02:23:25,225
Hey!

1821
02:23:29,933 --> 02:23:31,058
Hey!

1822
02:23:31,350 --> 02:23:34,892
Are you playing the fool with me?
I'll chop you into pieces!

1823
02:23:37,433 --> 02:23:39,475
- Sir, please--
- Hey!

1824
02:23:39,558 --> 02:23:41,767
- Sir.
- Why are you hanging up on me?

1825
02:23:41,850 --> 02:23:43,517
- Sir.
- What is going on there?

1826
02:23:43,600 --> 02:23:46,642
He's no ordinary fellow, sir.
He has set traps all around the house.

1827
02:23:46,725 --> 02:23:48,225
<i>All our men are dead.</i>

1828
02:23:48,808 --> 02:23:50,642
<i>I know him like the back of my hand.</i>

1829
02:23:50,725 --> 02:23:52,058
<i>I confirm, he is Leo.</i>

1830
02:23:52,142 --> 02:23:53,475
Who is in front of you?

1831
02:23:53,558 --> 02:23:56,433
His wife and daughter.
Shall I slit their throats open?

1832
02:23:56,517 --> 02:23:58,767
No need.
Put the phone on speaker.

1833
02:23:59,017 --> 02:24:00,600
<i>Give the phone to his wife.</i>

1834
02:24:03,683 --> 02:24:04,933
You better listen to me.

1835
02:24:05,017 --> 02:24:06,725
- Accept that you are Leo.
- Sir.

1836
02:24:06,808 --> 02:24:08,225
<i>I'll let them go.</i>

1837
02:24:09,767 --> 02:24:10,767
Parthi!

1838
02:24:14,058 --> 02:24:15,808
Sathya, don't panic.

1839
02:24:19,225 --> 02:24:20,433
Accept it.

1840
02:24:25,975 --> 02:24:27,683
Subramani.

1841
02:24:52,100 --> 02:24:53,267
Hey!

1842
02:24:53,350 --> 02:24:55,118
I'm talking seriously here
and you're laughing!

1843
02:24:55,142 --> 02:24:56,142
Me?

1844
02:24:57,017 --> 02:24:58,808
I think it's some rabid dog.

1845
02:25:01,683 --> 02:25:02,767
Go away!

1846
02:25:20,850 --> 02:25:24,058
I told you to instruct your men
to not go in, sir.

1847
02:25:24,142 --> 02:25:25,683
Poor fellows.
Right, sir?

1848
02:25:55,142 --> 02:25:57,017
Now the Leo we know will emerge.

1849
02:26:30,100 --> 02:26:33,058
Chittu, he has to accept that he's Leo.

1850
02:27:02,933 --> 02:27:06,100
- Don't let go of him!
- Hold him tight!

1851
02:27:06,183 --> 02:27:08,308
- Chop him!
- Don't let go of him.

1852
02:28:08,183 --> 02:28:09,558
Chop him into pieces!

1853
02:28:42,892 --> 02:28:44,725
Chop him!

1854
02:29:10,850 --> 02:29:12,517
Hey! Stay with his son.

1855
02:31:15,350 --> 02:31:16,475
Hey!

1856
02:31:16,725 --> 02:31:19,183
I used this to kill your sister--

1857
02:32:01,892 --> 02:32:03,600
Now I realise

1858
02:32:04,642 --> 02:32:06,183
you are not Leo.

1859
02:32:06,475 --> 02:32:08,017
You are Parthiban.

1860
02:32:08,933 --> 02:32:10,558
Now I believe you.

1861
02:32:10,850 --> 02:32:12,600
You are not the one

1862
02:32:14,933 --> 02:32:16,433
whom I was looking for.

1863
02:32:16,808 --> 02:32:18,183
Let's call it quits.

1864
02:32:18,558 --> 02:32:19,642
What do you say?

1865
02:32:20,808 --> 02:32:22,017
Drop your gun.

1866
02:32:22,808 --> 02:32:24,225
Hey!

1867
02:32:24,767 --> 02:32:26,433
Lower your gun.

1868
02:32:26,683 --> 02:32:27,892
Lower it.

1869
02:32:28,308 --> 02:32:30,850
Hey! Either shoot it
or drop it, scoundrel!

1870
02:32:30,975 --> 02:32:32,058
Let go!

1871
02:32:55,892 --> 02:32:58,808
<i>♪ Leo-- ♪</i>

1872
02:32:58,933 --> 02:33:01,058
<i>♪ Leo! ♪</i>

1873
02:33:02,267 --> 02:33:05,600
<i>♪ Leo! ♪</i>

1874
02:33:09,808 --> 02:33:14,225
- If I'm sweet, you're bloody sweet, Uncle.
- Hey!

1875
02:33:16,725 --> 02:33:19,600
I should've killed you
on that fateful day, right?

1876
02:33:20,642 --> 02:33:21,892
The mistake was mine.

1877
02:33:23,683 --> 02:33:24,683
Now go to hell!

1878
02:33:24,767 --> 02:33:29,808
<i>♪ Leo-- ♪</i>

1879
02:33:30,433 --> 02:33:32,267
Was this necessary for you?

1880
02:33:32,350 --> 02:33:35,100
"I want to see Leo.
I want to find Leo."

1881
02:33:36,433 --> 02:33:37,933
Didn't you ask?

1882
02:33:38,600 --> 02:33:39,725
See me now.

1883
02:33:39,808 --> 02:33:44,892
<i>♪ Leo-- ♪</i>

1884
02:33:56,017 --> 02:33:57,642
Drop your gun.

1885
02:34:09,475 --> 02:34:11,892
Check if there are any vehicles outside.

1886
02:34:16,892 --> 02:34:20,433
<i>If a person's past has to be quoted often</i>

1887
02:34:20,517 --> 02:34:22,475
<i>he should've done something good.</i>

1888
02:34:22,558 --> 02:34:24,558
<i>I have done no good deed.</i>

1889
02:34:25,100 --> 02:34:29,142
<i>In my past, knowingly or unknowingly,
I have committed many crimes.</i>

1890
02:34:29,600 --> 02:34:33,308
<i>The last chance I got to reform myself
is this family of mine.</i>

1891
02:34:33,975 --> 02:34:38,725
<i>I will go to any extent
to protect this family.</i>

1892
02:34:39,475 --> 02:34:42,308
<i>The man called Leo is dead.</i>

1893
02:34:42,517 --> 02:34:46,475
<i>If I have to convince this town
and the people around of his demise</i>

1894
02:34:46,933 --> 02:34:49,933
<i>first I have to believe it myself.</i>

1895
02:34:50,433 --> 02:34:53,767
<i>Leo is dead.
I believe it.</i>

1896
02:35:03,517 --> 02:35:05,183
How are you?

1897
02:35:08,517 --> 02:35:13,600
<i>No matter how many people
come and ask me if I'm Leo,</i>

1898
02:35:14,350 --> 02:35:16,642
<i>I'll convince them too.</i>

1899
02:35:18,767 --> 02:35:22,558
<i>Despite that, if someone
insists on knowing my story,</i>

1900
02:35:22,933 --> 02:35:26,225
<i>he should either die the next minute</i>

1901
02:35:26,892 --> 02:35:29,475
<i>or already be dead.</i>

1902
02:35:32,642 --> 02:35:34,725
Of course I'm Leo.

1903
02:35:35,433 --> 02:35:37,767
Leo Das!

1904
02:35:38,433 --> 02:35:40,725
<i>♪ My life is in this town ♪</i>

1905
02:35:40,808 --> 02:35:43,225
<i>♪ And I ain't going down ♪</i>

1906
02:35:43,308 --> 02:35:47,892
<i>♪ You think that I'm crazy
But I don't want the crown ♪</i>

1907
02:35:48,058 --> 02:35:50,433
<i>♪ My life is in this town ♪</i>

1908
02:35:50,558 --> 02:35:52,933
<i>♪ And I ain't going down ♪</i>

1909
02:35:53,017 --> 02:35:57,433
<i>♪ You think that I'm crazy
But I don't want the crown ♪</i>

1910
02:35:57,517 --> 02:36:00,725
<i>♪ Just an ordinary person ♪</i>

1911
02:36:01,100 --> 02:36:01,933
